<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER HOUSING ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the gear shift lever housing secured in a vise, install the spade pin in the bore
                    of the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13021a1">Figure 101</hotlnk>). If previously removed, install the O-ring in the
                    tower groove.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13021a1" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13021a1" filename="../figg13/G13021a1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 101. Spade Pin In Bore</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gear shift lever in the housing with the spade pin in the lever ball slot
                    and install the tension spring washer over the ball, dished-side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13021a2">Figure102</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13021a2" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13021a2" filename="../figg13/G13021a2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 102. Install Tension Spring Washer</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tension spring under the lugs in the housing,
                    <emph type="bold">seating one coil at a time</emph>
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13021a3">Figure 103</hotlnk>)
                    <emph type="bold">.</emph>
                    Use of a spring driving tool is recommended.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13021a3" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13021a3" filename="../figg13/G13021a3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 103. Install Tension Spring</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise and install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever
                    and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13021a4">Figure 104</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13021a4" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13021a4" filename="../figg13/G13021a4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 104. Install Rubber Boot</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
